
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the [stream] argument is true. If so, it updates the [.result] node by replacing occurrences of the string "stream" with "true" within its current value. The [if] slot evaluates the condition, and if true, the [set-value] and [strings.replace] slots perform the string replacement operation.
if:x:@.arguments/*/stream
   set-value:x:@.result
      strings.replace:x:@.result
         .:[[stream]]
         .:true
